Rating: 4
This is an exceptional recipe that tastes like it came from a bakery. The pastry has a delicate crumb that is really the sign of someone who knows what they're doing! That said, this recipe tired me out. I don't know why--it seems relatively straightforward. I prepared it along with some other recipes for a picnic, and maybe it was just too much at once. I did feel, though, that I'll reserve it only for special occasions. I loved the almond filling and don't understand why others didn't taste it.

