Rating: 3
It was great, but I made a few changes: I made it as a single 9" tart because I wanted to use my new pan, and I used my own pastry recipe (from the Betty Crocker cookbook, its really easy and rich). There was more than enough filling, and it was very rich and almondy. I cooked it for 35min, and I didn't dot with butter because of all the butter already in the crust and filling. Great!

