A dish beyond compare. The guests at my luncheon were all wowed by this relatively simple masterpeice. Making this tart was time well spent.

Rating: 4
I made these for a dinner party last weekend and they were a huge hit! I did use my own pastry recipe, however, which is very flaky and better than any I've tried in the past. I fanned out the peach slices and added fresh, plump blackberries. I reduced a can of peach nectar down to a glaze (about 1/4 cup) and glazed the tarts when they came out of the oven. I served these warm with a sprinkle of powdered sugar, scattered berries and a scoop of Dulce de Leche ice cream. I think this will work well with rasberries & blueberries too. This recipe is a keeper!

