Rating: 4
As others before me have said, this dish is a bit time consuming, but worth it. Once baked, the pastry held up wonderfully underneath the warm and luscious almond paste and peaches. The only mistake or oddity that I encountered was the recipe itself. Under the pastry ingredients it indicates that you should use "8 ounces (2 cups)" of flour. Based on the small amount of cooking that I have done, 8 oz. is the equivalence of 1 cup. I opted for the 8 oz. measurement and everything came out great.

